cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper discusses understanding the internal workings of deep neural networks in computer vision, which suggests that the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions exploring the intersection of inverse sets of several neurons, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper proposes an optimization-based sampling approach, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses understanding the concepts captured by a neuron, which suggests that it may belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions inspection of samples, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
